<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="118" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1782,1917]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1782,1808]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Mandible tridentate, inner margin without tooth; pronotal collar with (
<figureCitation box="[1060,1127,1783,1809]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[167,1419,184,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[167,1420,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Crossocerus (Thao) nitidicorpus indicus Saini &amp; Dey, subsp. nov. Holotype ♀. 9. Mesosoma, dorsal view; 10. Mesosoma, lateral view; 11. Propodeum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770976/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) or without trace of median notch; mesopleuron without precoxal denticle (
<figureCitation box="[686,770,1819,1845]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[167,1419,184,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[167,1420,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Crossocerus (Thao) nitidicorpus indicus Saini &amp; Dey, subsp. nov. Holotype ♀. 9. Mesosoma, dorsal view; 10. Mesosoma, lateral view; 11. Propodeum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770976/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
); tergum II with large round hollow depression at the base (
<figureCitation box="[159,232,1855,1881]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[194,1392,197,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[183,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Crossocerus (Thao) nitidicorpus indicus Saini &amp; Dey, subsp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Habitus, dorsal view; 3. Habitus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770968" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770968/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Figs 2</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[272,302,1855,1881]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1763,1787]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,294,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-67@6.[151,1435,272,1739]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Crossocerus (Thao) nitidicorpus indicus Saini &amp; Dey, subsp. nov. Holotype ♀. 12. Metasoma, lateral view; 13. Metasoma, dorsal view; 14. Metasoma, ventral view; 15. Pygidial plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770978" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770978/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">13</figureCitation>
); pygidial plate a narrow, isosceles triangle (
<figureCitation box="[819,904,1854,1881]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1763,1787]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,294,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-67@6.[151,1435,272,1739]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Crossocerus (Thao) nitidicorpus indicus Saini &amp; Dey, subsp. nov. Holotype ♀. 12. Metasoma, lateral view; 13. Metasoma, dorsal view; 14. Metasoma, ventral view; 15. Pygidial plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770978" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770978/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
), smooth, slightly depressed dorsally (
<bibRefCitation author="Tsuneki, K." pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="15 - 45" refId="ref3550" refString="Tsuneki, K. (1982) Studies on the new material of Sphecidae, Chrysididae and Mutillidae from Formosa and the Southern Ryukyus (Hymenoptera). Special Publications of the Japan Hymenopterists Association, 23, 15 - 45." type="journal article" year="1982">Tsuneki 1982</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Leclercq, J." box="[222,388,1891,1917]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="157 - 192" refId="ref3316" refString="Leclercq, J. (2009) Hymenopteres Crabroniens d'Asie du genre Crossocerus Lepeletier &amp; Brulle 1835 (Hymenoptera: Crabronidae Crabroninae). Entomologie faunistique - Faunistic Entomology, 61, 157 - 192. [in French]" type="journal article" year="2009">Leclercq 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
